Commit Message: Initial commit
Remove dead code
Add setters
Add some documentation
Update documentation on pypi

Fix typing issue

Can't use the class name for its own member functions.

Add basic support for quats

Allows quat parameters to be loaded and saved. Note that the lerp stuff
is currently ignored.
Remove some numbered names from hashed_names
Merge Zeikken's hashed_names

Guess names using numbered name strings

Numbered names (e.g. ClimateDefines_0) are common in AAMP files,
because the format lacks support for proper arrays.

These are put in a file that is separate from the regular
hashed_names.txt to avoid having to generate hundreds of entries
that differ only in the number and to avoid making having a huge list.
Bump version
Add some entries that were removed by mistake
Add support for curve parameters
Add AI to hashed_names

yaml_util: Test with indices that start with 1

For some reason Nintendo uses 1-based indices in some cases...
therefore we need to test indices up to idx + 1 (included),
not just idx.

yaml_util: Memoize numbered names guessing results

Sometimes the same keys are used in several objects. This allows us to
skip many redundant checks.
Add Tuta to hashed_names
main: Refactor arg parsing into separate functions

Add a single unified command for both conversions

And keep xxx_to_xxx for backwards compatibility reasons.
Bump version
yaml_util: Handle 'es' plurals
yaml_util: Handle more suffixes

numbered_names: Add State_%d

Used in rgbw
yaml_util: Test with 1-based indices

Add more names

DamageParam and a few other files don't have any unknown names anymore.

Write all parameter lists before writing objects

While not strictly necessary, this makes the layout of generated files
closer to Nintendo-produced files and prevents aamptool from choking
on them as it assumes "root nodes" (parameter lists) to be stored
contiguously (which is not guaranteed).

test_data: add a simpler AAMP with a complex structure

Adds an aiprog which, like all other aiprogs, uses lists, objects,
and nested parameter lists, but is shorter and thus simpler to
understand and analyse for debugging.
Add a script to test roundtrip conversion
Use versioneer for versioning
Extract converter functionality into reusable module

botw_hashed_names: Add "AS"

AS had been accidentally removed
Fix incorrect usage of open()

Optimize parsing by not tracking strings unless needed

Only keep track of strings if it is useful (i.e. when converting to
a human readable representation).

And get rid of useless encode() + decode() calls.

Remove _get_param_data_size

_get_param_data_size causes many unnecessary calculations and checks.
Simplify the parsing process by "inlining" the useful parts of it.

Optimise _parse_param_str

Use bytes.find() as a faster way to strlen().
Added get_bytes() to Writer for convenience
Update PyYAML dependency

ci: Add travis configuration file

test_data: Add aglccr file (to test curves)
Workaround for AAMP->YAML without names from reader
Use dataclasses for structures (#3)

Improve hash->name without reader

I looked more closely at how the AAMP reader is used in `_get_pstruct_name` and realized that I could keep most of the code to get names even without the reader, rather than just skipping to returning the hash.
Fix recursion in U32 `__repr__`
travis: Test on Python 3.7 and 3.8 too
Clean up trailing whitespace

Fix data corruption bug in parameter data reuse logic

Fixes a data corruption bug in the parameter data reuse logic that
could occur when a match with an offset that is not divisible by 4
is found. The offset writer would round down the offset to the
nearest multiple of 4, which results in data corruption.

This also adds offset representability checks to the placeholder
offset writers in order to catch similar bugs.

A test case has been added.

Fixes #7
